# Skill: deploy-github-pages

**Trigger:** User says "deploy", "publish app", "set up GitHub Pages", or "deploy to GitHub Pages".
**Standard:** Read `.claude/standards-git.md` before any deployment step.

> **Not automatic.** Run only on explicit user request — this skill modifies CI/CD configuration.

---

## Phase 1: Pre-Flight Check

**Branch Verification:** Ensure the active branch is `main` or a stable `feat/` branch.

**Build Audit:** Verify the project contains the build script for GitHub Pages (e.g. `build:gh-pages` in `package.json`).

**Environment Check:** Ensure the repository has a configured `gh-pages` branch or is set to deploy via GitHub Actions.

---

## Phase 2: Build & Optimization

**Clean Build:** Run `[BUILD_COMMAND]` with `--base-href [BASE_HREF]` to ensure assets resolve correctly on GitHub's sub-paths.

**Asset Check:** Verify `[BUILD_OUTPUT]` contains the correct `index.html` and bundled assets before proceeding.

---

## Phase 3: Deployment Execution

**Push to Branch:** Execute `npx gh-pages -d [BUILD_OUTPUT]` to publish to the `gh-pages` branch.

**Remote Sync:** Ensure the deployment commit is pushed to `origin`.

---

## Phase 4: URL Verification

**Link Generation:** Construct the final URL (`https://[github-user].github.io/[PROJECT_NAME]/`).

**Smoke Test:** Visually confirm icons and styles loaded correctly at the live URL.

---

## Completion Gate

Output: `"Deployment successful. App is live at: https://[github-user].github.io/[PROJECT_NAME]/"`

Update the session handoff with the deployment timestamp and version if applicable.
